hints.content: When we skip count by hundreds,  we add $100$ to each number as we count.

Easton started with $165$,  so we need to add $100$ more to $165$.

$165 + 100 =265$

The next number Easton will say is $265$.

Easton is still skip counting by hundreds so we need to add $100$ to $265$.

$265+ 100 =365$

The next number Easton will say is $365$.
